cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with channel state information (CSI) and optimal training design to maximize the transferred energy, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless energy transfer (WET) systems, which are a type of wireless network. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new two-phase channel training scheme to achieve diversity and beamforming gains, which involves control of the energy transmitter (ET) and energy receiver (ER) systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the transfer of energy over wireless channels, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require wireless power transfer. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper formulates and solves an optimization problem to maximize the net harvested energy, which involves computational methods and techniques.
